        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(imessage): route direct media captions through attachments",
        "body": "## Summary\n- route direct-handle iMessage media sends through chat resolution plus `send-attachment`\n- split captioned iMessage media into attachment delivery followed by a normal text send\n- keep explicit chat media-only attachment routing covered, and add regressions for direct media plus captions\n- clean up temporary outbound handoff copies after the send path finishes\n\nCloses #87597\n\n## Tests\n- `node_modules/.bin/vitest run extensions/imessage/src/send.test.ts --environment node --reporter=dot`\n  - 26 passed\n- `pnpm check:test-types`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.extensions.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions.tsbuildinfo`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- behavior: direct-handle iMessage media sends now route through `send-attachment`; captioned media sends deliver the attachment first and the caption as a separate normal text send. Temporary handoff copies are removed after the send path finishes.\n- environment: PR-head local checkout at `c67f998bc5`, macOS Messages/iMessage bot bridge, configured outbound handoff directory, existing direct 1:1 iMessage conversation. All personal identifiers are redacted from this PR.\n- steps: sent one media-only PNG to a direct iMessage handle through the PR-head `sendMessageIMessage` path, then sent captioned PNGs to the same direct-handle target through the same path. The harness recorded the invoked CLI command names, queried bot-visible Messages history, and checked the handoff directory for a uniquely named cleanup-test copy after send completion.\n- evidence: command instrumentation recorded `send-attachment` for direct media sends. Bot-visible history recorded outgoing `image/png` attachment rows with `missing:false`; captioned cases were followed by outgoing text rows containing the caption. The cleanup test reported no leftover handoff file for the uniquely named test attachment after send completion. The public PR intentionally omits phone numbers, real chat GUIDs, local user paths, and private message IDs.\n- observedResult: media-only direct send delivered a PNG attachment; captioned direct media delivered a PNG attachment followed by the caption text; the temporary handoff copy was removed after the send completed. This is the behavior that failed before the PR when direct-handle/captioned media fell through legacy RPC `send` with `file`.\n- notTested: group iMessage media delivery and reply-to media delivery were not live-tested in this pass; they are outside the direct-handle/caption bug fixed here and remain covered only by existing automated coverage.",
